    <sampling_method>Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Capable and willing to sign a consent form and participate in the study

          -  Subjects diagnosed as intermediate AMD in at least one eye

          -  Age &gt;50 years

          -  VA with habitual correction &gt;20/60 in the study eye

          -  Ability to speak, read and understand instructions in Hebrew

          -  Familiar with computer usage

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Evidence of macular disease other than AMD or glaucoma in the study eye

          -  Presence of any significant media opacity that precludes a clear view of the macular
             area as identified in the study eye by biomicroscopy, CFP.

          -  Any non-macular related ocular surgery performed within 3 months prior to study entry
             in the target eye

          -  Participation in another study with the exclusion of AREDS study

          -  Patients diagnosed with geographic atrophy (GA)
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
